.TH simple_shell 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
[\fICOMMAND\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic UNIX command interpreter written in C as part of the Holberton School curriculum.
It mimics the functionality of the standard shell, allowing the user to execute commands
in both interactive and non\-interactive modes.

The shell:
.IP \(bu 2
Displays a prompt and waits for the user to type a command.
.IP \(bu 2
Executes commands using
.BR fork (2)
and
.BR execve (2).
.IP \(bu 2
Handles the
.B PATH
environment variable to locate executables.
.IP \(bu 2
Implements built\-in commands:
.BR exit
and
.BR env .

.SH OPTIONS
This program has no options.
Use it as a standalone executable.

.SH EXAMPLES
Run the shell in interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
main.c shell.c README.md
($) exit
.fi

Run in non\-interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
main.c shell.c README.md
.fi

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Jawad Mohammad Alrajhi and Nawaf Saleh Alzahrani
as part of the Holberton School curriculum.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2)
